# Env Configuration Guide

## Environment Variables Reference

### Development Environment (.env.development)

```env
# Application
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000
APP_NAME=YouTube Clone
APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/youtube-clone

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=development_secret_key_not_for_production
JWT_EXPIRE=7d

# File Upload
MAX_FILE_SIZE=5368709120
UPLOAD_PATH=./public/uploads

# Azure (Optional for local)
AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_NAME=
AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_KEY=
AZURE_CONTAINER_NAME=videos
```

### Production Environment (.env.production)

```env
# Application
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000
APP_NAME=YouTube Clone
APP_URL=https://youtube-clone-app.azurewebsites.net

# Database - Use MongoDB Atlas
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/youtube-clone?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# JWT - Use strong secret
JWT_SECRET=use_strong_secret_generate_with_crypto
JWT_EXPIRE=7d

# File Upload
MAX_FILE_SIZE=5368709120
UPLOAD_PATH=./public/uploads

# Azure Storage
AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_NAME=yourstorageaccount
AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_KEY=your_storage_key
AZURE_CONTAINER_NAME=videos

# Security
SESSION_SECRET=strong_session_secret_key
CORS_ORIGIN=https://youtube-clone-app.azurewebsites.net

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=info
```

### Staging Environment (.env.staging)

```env
# Application
NODE_ENV=staging
PORT=3000
APP_NAME=YouTube Clone
APP_URL=https://youtube-clone-staging.azurewebsites.net

# Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/youtube-clone-staging

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=staging_secret_key_strong
JWT_EXPIRE=7d

# File Upload
MAX_FILE_SIZE=5368709120
UPLOAD_PATH=./public/uploads

# Azure Storage
AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_NAME=yourstorage
AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_KEY=key
AZURE_CONTAINER_NAME=videos-staging
```

## Azure App Service Configuration

### Using Azure CLI

```bash
# Set environment variables
az webapp config appsettings set \
  --resource-group youtube-clone-rg \
  --name youtube-clone-app \
  --settings \
    NODE_ENV=production \
    PORT=3000 \
    MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://user:pass@cluster.mongodb.net/youtube-clone" \
    JWT_SECRET="your_strong_secret_key" \
    JWT_EXPIRE="7d" \
    MAX_FILE_SIZE="5368709120" \
    UPLOAD_PATH="./public/uploads" \
    AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_NAME="yourname" \
    AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_KEY="yourkey" \
    AZURE_CONTAINER_NAME="videos"
```

### Using Azure Portal

1. Navigate to App Service
2. Settings → Configuration
3. Add application settings
4. Save changes

## MongoDB Connection Strings

### Local MongoDB
```
mongodb://localhost:27017/youtube-clone
```

### MongoDB Atlas
```
mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/youtube-clone?retryWrites=true&w=majority
```

## Generating Secure Secrets

### JWT Secret (Node.js)
```javascript
const crypto = require('crypto');
const secret = crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex');
console.log(secret);
```

### Session Secret
```bash
# Using openssl
openssl rand -hex 32

# Using Python
python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"

# Using Node
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```

## Best Practices

1. **Never commit .env files** - Add to .gitignore
2. **Use strong secrets** - 32+ character random strings
3. **Rotate secrets regularly** - Every 90 days
4. **Use Azure Key Vault** - For production secrets
5. **Different secrets per environment** - Dev/Staging/Prod
6. **Document required variables** - Create .env.example
7. **Use environment-specific files** - .env.local, .env.prod
8. **Restrict file permissions** - chmod 600 .env

## Azure Key Vault Integration

```bash
# Create Key Vault
az keyvault create \
  --resource-group youtube-clone-rg \
  --name youtube-clone-vault

# Add secret
az keyvault secret set \
  --vault-name youtube-clone-vault \
  --name MongoDbUri \
  --value "mongodb+srv://user:pass@..."

# Reference in App Service
# @Microsoft.KeyVault(VaultName=youtube-clone-vault;SecretName=MongoDbUri)
```

## Validation

The application validates these environment variables on startup:
- NODE_ENV (development|staging|production)
- PORT (number)
- MONGODB_URI (valid MongoDB connection)
- JWT_SECRET (string, min 10 chars)

## Troubleshooting

### "MONGODB_URI is not set"
- Check if .env file exists
- Verify MONGODB_URI in .env
- Restart application

### "Invalid JWT secret"
- Ensure JWT_SECRET is set
- Minimum 10 characters recommended
- 32+ for production

### Connection timeouts
- Check MongoDB is running/accessible
- Verify firewall rules
- Test connection string with mongosh

